Step 1: Identify Total Liabilities and Total Assets at the end of the reporting period.
• From the balance sheet, Total Assets (End_amount) = 29,133,140.32.
• The liabilities available in the table are listed under Accounts Payable and Taxes Payable. Since Accounts Payable is 0.00 and Taxes Payable is 727,140.68, the Total Liabilities (End_amount) = 727,140.68.

Step 2: Use the formula for the Debt to Asset Ratio.
  Debt to Asset Ratio = (Total Liabilities) / (Total Assets)

Step 3: Substitute the values.
  Debt to Asset Ratio = 727,140.68 / 29,133,140.32 ≈ 0.02498

Step 4: Round the ratio to two decimal places.
  0.02498 rounded to two decimals is 0.02.

Thus, the Debt to Asset Ratio as of the end of the reporting period is 0.02.
